media.altText:
Image description: 

[ Yes it is important to be able to validate yourself - but can we please stop taking that fact to the extreme of acting like you're failing at self love if you need some degree of validation and support from other people? I mean we're social animals before we're individuals and that's actually ok. I am so tired of "you shouldn't need anyone's validation but your own" posts because we should and we do and adding shame to having those needs doesn't change the fact that we're social animals by nature. ] 

End of image description
